President Obama has nominated four individuals to serve on the United States District Courts. The nominees are Stephen R. Bough for the Western District of Missouri, Richard Franklin Boulware II for the District of Nevada, Judge Salvador Mendoza, Jr. for the Eastern District of Washington, and Staci Michelle Yandle for the Southern District of Illinois. Each nominee has a background in law and brings experience in various areas of legal practice. President Obama expressed confidence in their ability to serve with integrity and a commitment to justice.